for excitement lisa’s career took a turn for the best when relocated by wunderman to help start the creative department for their latin american office located in miami lisa moved to ogilvy  mather and spent the next  years traveling through latin america shooting television commercials in  lisa started vertigo media group a fullservice marketing communications firm with a strong concentration on brand advertising vertigo specializes in branding young companies along with reinvigorating existing brands as an expert in the industry she has given many seminars on marketing most recently to the long island direct marketing association lisa has spoken at hofstra university and farmingdale university to young graduates looking to start their careers in marketing dedicated to her community vertigo media group has helped raise funds and donated graphic services to foundations such as the liday breast cancer foundation the sepe foundation the port washington library foundation and the long island elite lisa also sits on the board of the long island inventors club suffolk county chapter and has been a committee member two years running with the long island elite where she has played a vital role in raising tens of thousands of dollars for many local long island charities as a mother of two leo  and gianna  lisa is a member of the pta and an assistant coach for her daughter’s cheerleading squad   fred pesce – executive vice president  creative director after serving in the us navy as a veteran of desert storm fred pesce received his bachelor of arts in graphic design from the school of visual arts in nyc graduating in the top ten of his class upon graduation fred worked for a major advertising and direct marketing agency as senior art director in his  years at the agency he developed campaigns and marketing material for a variety of industries – from boutique shops to fortune  companies clients ranged from major banks and catering establishments to spas and hitech companies i